|CKBStreet Samurai Progression|000

|CK0Street Samurai have 16 Guild Levels and 200 Cortex Ranks. GXP comes from
combat and boss victories recognized by Darkwind's shared battle progression.
Repeating firmware commands does not award GXP.|000

|CKBGuild Level and Cortex Rank|000
|CK0Use samxp or gscore to see Guild Level, Cortex Rank, current GXP, and the
next rank requirement. Through the early ranks, Cortex Rank also advances
Guild Level. If a character-level requirement temporarily blocks an early
Guild Level, earned GXP remains banked and advancement resumes when the
requirement is met.|000

|CK0After GL16, Guild Level remains fixed while Cortex Rank continues through
CR200. Later Cortex Ranks take more sustained combat progress. The host OS
continues gaining bounded throughput improvements across that full progression,
but hardware grade,
character capabilities, Heat, and maintenance still matter independently.
Dashboard reports the current Cortex throughput.|000

|CKBUnlocks|000
|CK0Firmware and signature implants unlock from GL1 through GL16. Prototype
hardware is available first, followed by street grade at GL7, military grade
at GL10, and ghost grade at GL13. The paired routine's Guild Level can still
delay a specific implant even when its grade is otherwise available.|000

|CKBWhen progress seems stalled|000
|CK0Check samxp for the current requirement, confirm the contract is active,
and continue fighting opponents that the shared battle system recognizes as
appropriate progression. Samskills shows the next routine unlock; Rin Kade's
catalog shows hardware that is available now and future contract unlocks.|000
